qas.question: Often, how large a part of the structure of a gene is the protein coding sequence?
What often plays only a small part in the structure of a gene?
What is one of the many elements that the structure of a gene consists of?

answers.text: DNA regions that are not transcribed

qas.question: What is another element of the structure of a gene?
What elements does the structure of a gene consist of?

answers.text: DNA regions that are not transcribed as well as untranslated regions of the RNA
